Beat cream cheese in large bowl with mixer until creamy. Gradually add milk, beating until well blended. Add dry pudding mixes; beat on low speed 1 min. or until well blended. Cover bottom of 13x9-inch pan with half the ladyfingers; top with layers of half each of the pudding mixture, COOL WHIP DIPS and berries. Repeat all layers. Refrigerate 3 hours. Sprinkle with chocolate.